HEADWORD: Preëngagement
<hw>Pre`⟦eum⟧n*gage"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Prior
engagement, obligation, or attachment, as by contract, promise, or
affection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My <qex>pre⟦eum⟧ngagements</qex> to other themes were not unknown
to those for whom I was to write.</q> <rj><qau>Boyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preerect</ent>⟦br⟧
